:::summary
Ancient Rome was one of the most powerful and enduring civilizations in human history, spanning from its legendary founding in 753 BC to the fall of the Western Empire in AD 476. Rome's legal systems, governmental structures, language (Latin), and engineering feats shaped Western civilization — and it was the setting for the mortal ministry and crucifixion of Jesus Christ, as well as the early Christian Church.
:::

